    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-21T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-21T23:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/1806: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-21T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 21, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 22—1:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>705. For the Under Secretary. Department’s 540, December 21 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >20</hi>], noon. In a conversation this afternoon Dr. Solf<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d399fn5">Alfredo Solf y Muro, President of the Peruvian Council and
                        Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> asked what additional protection we had
                    in mind for Talara fearing that the suggested arrangement might provoke attacks.
                    He was also disturbed at the prospects of Peru having to take a stand prior to
                    the Rio Conference.<note n="6" xml:id="d399fn6">Third Meeting of the Foreign
                        Ministers of the American Republics, held at Rio de Janeiro, January 15–28,
                        1942. For preliminary correspondence, see <ref target="frus1941v06#pg_118"
                            >vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, pp. 118</ref> ff.</note> However, I
                    am hopeful that some satisfactory plan can be worked out fairly promptly
                    although a Cabinet decision will be necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
